\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid13721723 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13721723 GENERAL}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-720\li720\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid12403641 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15932980 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 1.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 During the last four weeks public opinion and morale, already very low owing to past physical and psychological strains, was most decisively influenced by the various stag
es through which the London Conference of Foreign Ministers passed to its jarring and sobering finale. Now that the many disturbing and threatening implications of its failure are beginning to sink in, the population is abandoning itself to a climactic se
n
se of despair and foreboding hitherto unreached. Prayer and cynicism together with a bitter awareness of dependence and impotence marked the opening of the Conference and accompanied it along its agonised and frustrated way to a burial with little hope of
 resurrection. To-day it is appreciated that the end of Germany's bitter road is not yet in sight and that it is entering a new and difficult year poorer in physical strength and moral resistance, in national and social purposes and in faith and hope.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 2.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Few view the outcome of the Conference otherwise than as the begin
ning of a series of trials which are unpredictable both as to direction and ultimate result. No one doubts, however, that the slow and painful beginning made, principally by the Anglo-S
axon powers, to recast Germany in a new democratic Europe will be halted, and perhaps completely nullified, by the march of events.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 3.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 In the field of immediate concerns it is realised that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
breakdown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  of the Conference spells the end of earlier h
opes for a unified Germany under a Central Government - a Germany whose economic and social needs might have been better served without the restricting effects of conflicting Zonal directions in the field of industry and agriculture, finance and exports a
nd on recovery in every sphere of national, social and moral health. Hopes for the miraculous restoration of Germany's eastern provinces have now entirely faded in the face of present develop
ments which have even put to question the efficacy of the Marshall Plan to bring stability to an uneasy Western Europe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 4.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
In fact, few believe the Western Allies to be in a position to enforce and sustain, if necessary in precarious balance, policies and decisions which would not only safeguard German interests 
in Western Europe but from which a gradual shift to more favourable balance might}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
be expected. It is felt that the main strength of power and resolve must come from the U.S.A., that Britain, even in conjunction with her European Allies, could not hope to a
nswer single-handed and successfully a determined challenge. The U.S A. is remote, the U.S.S.R. in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
close proximity. These facts, plus German appreciation of Russian strength and concentration of purpose, of her material, human and political resources and the subversive potential which flows from them, are the principal factors activating German fears.

\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15932980 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15932980 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 5.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
There can be little doubt that the people of Hamburg are badly frightened by the prospects of a development which it is felt may in its consequences surpass the experiences of the past two and a half years. A small minority which, even against inst
inct and painful realisation, had had visions of a new and democratic Germany, now see their broader hopes endangered. The majority exhaust their desperate anxiety which often borders on silent panic, in an inarticulate and morale destroying concern for t
he future.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 6.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
In this crisis, few are inclined to weigh anew whether conviction and/or expediency do not demand a strengthening of ties to the Occupying Power whose natural affinities with Western Germany remain, or should have remained, unaffected by 
the criticism and distrust with which many of its single measures have been met. But the great majority have sunk to a state where lack of hope, and cynicism, the bitter fruits of frustration, have long since convinced then that every nation's interests a
nd purposes are essentially selfish and that democracy, if not an outright sham, is only for those who can afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 7.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Consciousness of their dependence in every sphere, hating their role as an object in this conflict and in general, the German feel abandoned and ostracized. Irrespective of developments in other fields, this alone constitutes a grave danger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 FOOD
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 8.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641   }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
The food position in Hamburg has progressively worsened during the last six weeks; resulting hardships are accentuated by th
oughts of other Christmasses in happier times. The situation is further aggravated by growing difficulties in obtaining such rations as are available. As always, the general morale is vitally affected by conditions in this respect and is, in consequence, 
extremely low.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 9.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
The growing bitterness and distrust of the population in respect of the food situation is mainly directed to the farmers and shopkeepers. The farmer is accused of contributing heavily to the Black Market and therefore being unable an
d unwilling to deliver his quota. The shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 keeper is charged with becoming more and more inconsiderate of the popu
lation generally and with being involved in Black Market practices and the giving of preferential treatment for his own selfish ends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 10.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Principal complaints centre on the insufficient provision of fats, the entire absence of potatoes for the last six or eight weeks and failure to provide substitutes or equivalents for these two vital food}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 stuffs. There is also a great deal of discont
ent because the issue of milk powder and egg powder for which the population registered four weeks ago, have not yet materialised. The situation is aggravated by the fact that many shops have been stocked with milk powder for approximately one month. Rumo
ur has it that supplies of milk powder from, U.S.A have already deteriorated to such an extent that they are now only fit for the production of margarine. While the remainder of rationed food}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 stuffs have more or less been constantly available, further short
ages in addition to the present principal ones are anticipated. This applies particularly to the meat ration which it is though will be endangered when the supply from recent peak slaughterings is exhausted arid the provision of cereals which, it is belie
ved, will be seriously affected by coal shortages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 11.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Generally, it is felt that Hamburg as a declared emergency area is being mocked by an array of facts which contradict her status and widen the discrepancy between conditions prevailing within the Hansestadt and those outside her immediate boundaries.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 12.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
A special feature of the present position is that the first time since they were issued, this month's heavy workers rations were often unavailable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 FUEL
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 13.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 In contrast to the food position, there has been a marked improve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15932980 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
ent in the supply of fuel to private households as compared with last winter. This is due both to better supplies and the less severe weather. However, complaints continue in respect of the frequent and irregular interruptions in electricity supplies.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 14.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
In consequence of the leak of fuel, many laundries are refusing to take work. In view of the shortage of soap and the rationing and frequent unavailability of electricity and gas, this poses a special problem for the much harassed housewife. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 15.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Hamburg opticians who require regulated room temperature for the carrying out of certain processes are complaining that they are receiving no fuel. They point out that many email industries producing un}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 essential items such as ashtrays, etc., are receiving fuel while their profession, which serves in the interests of public health, is left without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 PUBLIC HEALTH 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 16.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Continuous and long term malnutrition, deplorable housing conditions, shortages of clothing, soap and hot water, etc., is caus
ing great concern to the Public Health Authorities. It has been feared for some time that T.B. has reached frightening dimensions from which permanent damage will result. It is known that the number of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
active T.B. cases and deaths at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 tributable to T.B. con
tinue to rise. It is doubted whether the total number of persons who are so far only slightly infected with T.B. is known. Hamburg Public Health Authorities have made considerable efforts to detect T.B. in its early stages by X-raying whole groups of the 
population. It is claimed, however, that these activities are seriously hampered by shortages of X-ray films and fuel for those places in which T.B. examinations take place.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 17.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Similar anxieties are entertained with regard to venereal diseases. It is 
thought that cases of syphilis are on the increase. However, the number of cases of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 gonorrhoea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  is declining and this is popularly attr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 buted to regular and growing supplies of penicillin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 HOUSING AND REQUISITIONING
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 18.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 The recent announcement tha
t further living accommodation was being requisitioned in Othmarschen, Hochkamp and Rahlstedt has caused such comment. There is still a widespread belief that many houses and flats requisitioned a considerable time ago have never been put to use. In}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 stance
s cited concern one house in Othiearschen, Hagedornstrasse 6, (uninhabited since August 1946); 17 three-roomed flats in Kochmannstr. uninhabited since February 1947; 10 eight-roomed flats in Oderfelderstr. uninhabited since May 1947. further uninhabited l
iving accommodation is said to be located. in Badestrasse and Innocentiastrasse. It is observed that requisitionings continue in spite of Burgermeister BRAUER's request for Military Government to refrain from requisitioning new premises be
fore the available accommodation has been fully occupied. The announcement has also served to keep alive complaints that only a fraction of the Four Seasons Hotel is being utilized.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 BUILDING 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 19.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 While old and oft-reiterated complaints as to the state of building
 and repairs in Hamburg live on, repeated attention has been drawn lately to the to the fact that many houses (especially emergency accommodation, are still without window-panes, whereas cinemas, theatres, restaurants and shop windows have largely been re
s
tored. It is also complained that a number of vacant houses and new buildings have been fully glazed in spite of the fact that few old people and children have been living in houses which are inadequately provided with glass. This has been taken as a furt
her indication that German Local Authorities are either without a plan or governed by instructions which ignore the public welfare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 CLOTHING
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 20.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Next to food and fuel, clothing and household articles are of principal concern. The existing situatio
n where the few available goods appear to go to the highest bidder remains unchanged. As old stocks wear out, the clamour for better supplies of everyday commodities swells. It appears that much of its force is no longer exclusively directed against Milit
ary Government but that the German Authorities are coming in for an ever-growing share of criticism.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 21.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
With the advent of winter, the footwear situation has been worsened. The shoe repair shops are unable to cope with public requirements and still l
ess able to adhere to prices fixed for the carrying out of repairs. Materials can often only be acquired on the Black Market and prices are raised accordingly. Promised fuel for the heating of repair shops has so far failed to materialize and if fuel is p
urchased on the Black Market; the customer has to foot the bill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 22.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
The fish and affiliated industries are suffering from a shortage of rubber footwear and waterproof garments. It is claimed that the Hamburg firm of ELSNER recently offered certain qua
ntities of rubbers and wooden shoes to a number of firms but the firms in question were unable to persuade the Landeswirtschaftsamt to issue the required number of coupons. This attitude is not understood by the general public. A great measure of public o
p
inion, not unsupported by various Landeswirtschaftsdmter, favours the removal of controls on kettles, buckets, saucepans, bowls, frying pans, cutlery, stoves, electric heaters, wooden bedsteads, radio valves, perambulators, clocks, razor blades, shoe lace
s, etc. This feeling is based on the argument that these goods are either available in sufficient quantities or in such short supply that the expense of administering their control is economically unjustified.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 23.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 The paper shortage continues to have a
n adverse effect on education in that the demand for school manuals and exercise book's remains far in excess of supply. Paper shortages are also said to be responsible for the fact that the Largest of the six match factories in the British Zone is workin
g to only 50% of its capacity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 BLACK MARKET
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 24.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Complaints continue that it is possible to obtain the best of food, wines and spirits in the Hamburg restaurants at Black Market prices. Prices are said to range from RM 20 for a cup of coffee to brandy at RM350 per bottle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 25.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 In general a go
od deal of talk has been heard to the effect that black marketeers have over-estimated the buying power of the population and that many are finding it difficult to dispose of their goods at current high prices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 26.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 The finger of suspicion has been fre
quently pointed to the German Courts where, it is believed, black marketeers are not only leniently treated but find the kind of assistance which implies corruption of judges and court officials.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 27.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 The dinner given by the trade unions to the Chambe
r of Commerce a few weeks ago, at which several courses of excellent quality and quantity together with fine old wines were served, has caused some curiosity as to the origin of these supplies. It is said that the dinner took place at the Hauptbahnhof res
taurant which was well-known in peacetime for the excellence of its cuisine. Some believe that the food and wines were made available by the Hamburg Co-operative Society. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 28.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Wage and salary earners continue to complain that travel to and from work is
 made difficult by the number of persons undertaking }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7604142 non-essential}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  journeys. It frequently has}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7604142 
 been suggested that Railway Com}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 panies should run trains with special coaches or compartments reserved for season ticket holders. The consensus of opinion seems 
to be that the Occupational Authorities are deliberately trying to curb rail traffic by keeping trains as uncomfortable and train schedules as inconvenient as possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 MILITARY GOVERNMENT
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7604142 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 29.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Following the trial of the former Hamburg Oberlande
sgerichts President, Kurt ROTHENBERGER, at Nuremberg, considerable attention has been given to the clearing of Nazi traces and influences from the German legal world. The consensus of opinion is that military Government has been badly advised in these mat
ters and true to its maxim "Control not Government" should have left it to the Germans to take the necessary action.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15932980 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 30.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
As an example, the case of the former Hamburger General Staatsanwalt HAACK is cited. Many Hamburgers expected to see HAACK on trial at Nurem}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
berg instead of which he was interned for a short time and was, it is claimed, then confirmed by Military Government as legal adviser in Neuengamme to internees appearing before the Spruchkammer at Bergedorf. Further, that owing to German pressu
re this confirmation was later withdrawn. Nevertheless, a point is made that HAACK, who must have enjoyed the special confidence of the Nazi regime to have been entrusted with clearing up the murder of HEYDRICH in the former German Protectorate of Bohemia
, was sufficiently and clearly "compromised' to such a degree as to preclude him from any possible consideration by Military Government.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid7604142 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 31.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 A recent order that all cigars and cigarettes and all coffee over one kilo in weight sent to Germans from abroa
d will be confiscated is meeting with violent reaction. A number of tense confiscations have already taken place and those who are left with a Military Government receipt in place of the tobacco or coffee feel that they nave additional cause for being cri
tical, if not openly hostile to Military Government.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-11\li0\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid15932980 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 LOCAL AUTHORITIES
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 32.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Complaints and criticism of German local Authorities are increasing rather than decreasing. The Landeswirtschaftsamt remain the principal target and is often contemptuousl
y spoken of as "hiding behind Minden or the British". It is also accused of being the special preserve for functionaries of the S.P.D. and Herr BORGENER's statement that it would be impossible to distribute American relief supplies by Christmas has certa
inly not lessened public distrust.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 33.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Lack of bicycle tyres, of which more are thought to reach the Black Market than the free market, has been singled out as a further proof of the inefficiency and/or corruption prevalent in many German agencies. Th
e Phonix Works at Harburg are frequently mentioned in this connection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 34.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Burgermeister BRAUER's pointed reference to the over-staffed administrative machinery of the Hansestadt}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 (50,000 persons working for the Hansestadt - 50,000 for Military Govern
ment) in a recent speech to an S.P D. meeting was well received, as it gave support to the belief that a dominating bureaucracy has installed itself in civic affairs to the detriment of the common wea1d
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 35.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 A measure of public hope and confidence is
 attached to the return of Dt. WOHLWILL from his London exile and it is anticipated that he will be able to restore the Hamburg legal administration to a semblance of its former high reputation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 DENAZIFICATION
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 36.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
In the field of denazification growing numbers of the population either show a complete lack of interest provided, they can afford it, or view its gymnastics with increasing cynicism and distrust. Many Denazification Panel members appear to share 
this general weariness mainly for the reason that their decisions and recommendations are nullified or ignored by decisions on appeal to Review Boards. It is claimed that Review Boards are susceptible to considerations which defeat the whole purpose of De
n
azification and that the presence of legally qualified. persons acting as judges or defending counsel make hearings the occasion for legal exercise at the expense of their proper political and social functions. The best legal talent is enlisted in cases w
here the property or wealth of former Nazis is involved and no expense is spared in these cases where there is a reasonable hope of safeguarding or recovering the principal part of the value at stake.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 37.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Criticism is also directed at Spruchkammern wh
ose sentences are either thought to be too lenient or too easily reduced on an appeal supported by the best legal minds. It is often commented that many solicitors of whom not a few are former "nominal" members of the N.S.D.A.P. are very busy attempting t
o rehabilitate former active Nazis and not in frequently give written testimonials in their favour.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 All this under}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15932980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 lines a tendency which has been known to exist for a long time that not inconsiderable numbers of the population are by no means adverse to re
storing former Nazis to their full social status and desire to be on good terms with them. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 SUBVERSIVE ACTIVITIES
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 38.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Nothing has come to notice which would point to an increase in organised subversive activities on the part of former Nazis. Opin
ion which is concerned with this danger inclines to the view that such circles of Nazis that remain intact have called for a moratorium in view of the present international situation. It is felt that this abstention is conditioned in the belief that criti
cal issues are imminent and that it is preferable to conserve all energies for a later date.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 REFUGEES AND EXPELLEES
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 39.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 It is generally believed that the breakdown of the London Confer
ence will result in the British and American Zones being swamped by large numbers of refugees from the Russian zone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
If this occurs it is unlikely that these people will meet with much sympathy from an indigent population which has been hardened to a point of insensibility to the distress of others by the may person
al difficulties and frustrations of the last few years. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 40. Meanwhile, former residents of the German eastern provinces complain that German banks in Hamburg are refusing to honour claims to funds deposited in their branch banks located in these terr
itories. The hardship is undeniable, the clamour understandable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 ECONOMY
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 41.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
The state of business and the morale of businessmen are equally affected by the present impasse and the political developments of the past few weeks. Hopes for an econom
ic recovery are being threatened by the possibility of a new conflagration which many fearfully prophesy. 
\par Meanwhile most businessmen live from hand to mouth and almost all current business activity is characterised by practices and conditions which an ordered economy would not tolerate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 42.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Note is being taken of an increase of advertisements offering good positions to German technicians and other skilled workers particularly in South America. Most of these advertisements appear under box numbers and
 it appears that serious consideration is being given to the taking up of such employment especially by young men and women, graduates from universities\rquote 
, technical institutes, etc., who, under present conditions, have little faith in making a future for themselves in Germany.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 43.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Hamburg exporters claim that the bureaucratic confusion within the Joint Export Import Agency is so great that contacts made with business}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
men abroad fail to produce results as most foreign businessmen refuse to be hamstrung by the J.E.I.A.S. exasperating methods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 44.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Businessman also condemn the special consideration given to Co-operative Societies in the allocation of supplies (allegedly as means of rehabilitating their business) and the levying of taxes.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 They hold that all business has been hard-hit by the war and its aftermath and that the
\par practice of favouring socialized enterprises is a denial of democracy and the principles of free economy alike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 POLICE
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 45.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 There has been surprisingly little attention paid to the handing over of control of the Hamburg Police.}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 This may be due to the fact that the population in general are not yet sufficiently aware or proud of the Police as a Hamburg institution to fo
llow their development with much interest. Criticism of the Police continues to the effect that many of its members are too young and inexperienced to guide and help a "jittery" population and that the Force still contains many in its ranks who are open t
o graft and corruption.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
A number have remarked that the brusque attitude of officers towards the other ranks which formerly characterised the German police is again becoming apparent and that the relationship between higher and lower officials is deteriorating as a result.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 46.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Many rumours continue to circulate to the effect that the lack of security in the streets at night is so considerable that many citizens either do not leave their houses after dark or traverse the streets armed with sticks, clubs, etc.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 The number of robberies is probably considerably less than is popularly imagined.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12403641 The public believes that they are carried out mainly with the object of obtaining clothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 EDUCATION AND YOUTH
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 47.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Senator LANDAHL, Head of the Hamburg Schu
lverwaltung, is the target for a good deal of criticism. A great many leading educationalists including the head of the Volkshochschul, VOGT, and Professor MERCK, have violently clashed with LANDAHL.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 It is generally believed that LANDAHL would not have obtained his present position if he had not joined the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7604142  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
S.P.D. He is charged with autocratic and overbearing conduct and appears to antagonise many of his subordinates by his vanity and reluctance to delegate responsibility.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 48.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Mention has been made of y
oung students, especially of the technical sciences, who are unable to chart their way after taking their final examinations. Most of them have no chance of obtaining the type of employment for which they have prepared and are forced to work either as}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7604142  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 arti
sans or labourers to qualify for rations. It is thought that good conditions of employment are being offered to those who are prepared to emigrate to the Russian Zone.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12403641 Up to now few have done so.
