\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 49.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 While it is generally a
cknowledged that the press of the British Zone enjoys a measure of freedom in reporting and commenting on news, it is felt that the total number of copies of newspapers is insufficient and that the restricted size of newspapers prohibits full coverage bei
ng
\par given to news, etc. This perpetuates the question as to whether the quantity of paper available to the British Zone is allocated in a manner which helps to serve primary interests and concerns before secondary ones. It is often said that more and larger 
newspapers and more and better literature could be made available if less paper were wasted in publishing fashion magazines, popular lyrics and crossword puzzles, etc. which appear to be available in unlimited quantities.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 50.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 Suggestions continue to
 be made to the effect that "Die Brucke", which is widely considered a useful and worthwhile instrument in the furtherance of German understanding of foreign and international problems, should have a number of branches established throughout the
\par Hansestadt. This military Government experiment is one of the few which has met with the wholehearted approval of the Germans. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 RUMOURS
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 51.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
Lately, there has been a dearth of rumours and this fact has not remained unnoticed in Hamburg. The absence of rumours has been attributed to general apathy and the prevailing state of resignation.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 It is also taken as a sign of the prevalence of a form of exhaustion in which rumour and humour alike no longer play their part as a means of relief.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
