Comment continues that many former Nazis and professional soldiers are succumbing to concentrated French efforts to recruit them
 into the Foreign Legion. It is frequently said that decent Germans are finding it difficult to go abroad while German war criminals are offered refuge putting them outside the reach of German justice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 53.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 A rumour to the effect that the Waiting Room
 at Altona Station which is now being used as a canteen for troops and other allied personnel is being returned to the Germans shortly, has found a sympathetic ear. It is believed that the present canteen is being moved to the Caf\'e9
 HIRTE which as at present being run by an old National Socialist and profiteer of the Hitler regime. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15932980 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 54.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641 
A number of unusually well-informed people claim to know that approximately three months ago, 35 former U-boat commanders were moved to No. 6 C.I.C Neuengamme. Soon afte
r their arrival, they learned through the camp grapevine that they would be asked whether they were prepared to serve a foreign power in the event of war; and oath of silence on the
\par matter would be imposed on them. Before the interview a meeting was held in the Camp in which a Nazi leader enjoined them to answer the question in the negative.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12403641  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12403641 It is said that this advice was accepted and that as a result they were subjected to a torrent of abuse from the British Camp Sergeant. 
